currentDoc:
Is Listening to a Book Just as Good as Reading It?

Do you listen to audiobooks? What are the benefits, in your opinion, of listening instead of reading? Are there advantages to reading that cannot be gained by listening? Which method do you prefer? Why?

---

In my opinion,

currentSuggestions.original: For example, some people read on the treadmill and listen to audiobooks; if you're a hard core reader, I don't see any advantages
currentSuggestions.trimmed: For example, some people read on the treadmill and listen to audiobooks; if you're a hard core reader, I don't see any advantages

currentSuggestions.original: For me, listening in the car, I don't get much out of it, as I am not in control of when the recording stops.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: For me, listening in the car, I don't get much out of it, as I am not in control of when the recording stops.

currentSuggestions.original: For example, driving can easily be done while listening to an audiobook.

currentSuggestions.original: If you feel like reading publicly, you read.

currentSuggestions.original: But I prefer to listen to audiobooks when I'm doing mindless tasks, like washing the dishes or folding laundry.

currentSuggestions.trimmed: However, I don’t believe there are advantages to listening that cannot be gained by reading.

currentSuggestions.original: At my desk, reading is the major activity.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: At my desk, reading is the major activity.

ops.insert: But I prefer to listen to audiobooks when I'm doing mindless tasks, like washing the dishes or folding laundry.

currentSuggestions.original: Listening to an audiobook definitely comes in handy in the summer when you have more time to lie out in the sun and read a book.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Listening to an audiobook definitely comes in handy in the summer when you have more time to lie out in the sun and read a book.

currentSuggestions.original: I find that, after reading for a while, I can tell what's going to happen next because I already know what the author is telling me.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: I find that, after reading for a while, I can tell what's going to happen next because I already know what the author is telling me.

currentSuggestions.original: Reading actively involves deciphering the words as you read, while listening requires active attention and forces you to imagine the words and images in your head instead of
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Reading actively involves deciphering the words as you read, while listening requires active attention and forces you to imagine the words and images in your head instead of

currentSuggestions.original: I'm often surprised by the experiences readers and listeners alike have with audiobooks.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: I'm often surprised by the experiences readers and listeners alike have with audiobooks.

currentSuggestions.original: Essentially, reading forces your brain to not only process the language and syntax of written words, but to then turn it into an image.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Essentially, reading forces your brain to not only process the language and syntax of written words, but to then turn it into an image.

currentSuggestions.original: When I read, I get caught up in the thoughts of the protagonist and the overall mood of the book.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: When I read, I get caught up in the thoughts of the protagonist and the overall mood of the book.

currentSuggestions.original: I find that I retain much more from a book I have read, rather than listened to it, though the former takes much more time than the latter
currentSuggestions.trimmed: I find that I retain much more from a book I have read, rather than listened to it, though the former takes much more time than the latter

currentSuggestions.original: Both are useful cognitive activities, and I recommend doing both when necessary.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Both are useful cognitive activities, and I recommend doing both when necessary.

currentSuggestions.original: Which do you prefer?
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Which do you prefer?

currentSuggestions.original: I find that reading is better for comprehension, especially if the book or article is difficult.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: I find that reading is better for comprehension, especially if the book or article is difficult.

currentSuggestions.original: I have to be ready to suddenly stop and start the audio again when driving or while doing things around the house.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: I have to be ready to suddenly stop and start the audio again when driving or while doing things around the house.

currentSuggestions.original: I must sit through the speaker’s interpretation of the material, and can only stop at specific intervals.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: I must sit through the speaker’s interpretation of the material, and can only stop at specific intervals.

currentSuggestions.original: I must be ready to yield to the reading speed and allow myself to get through a much larger amount of material in a shorter amount of time.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: I must be ready to yield to the reading speed and allow myself to get through a much larger amount of material in a shorter amount of time.

currentSuggestions.original: the words are processed by my ears and absorbed instantly into my brain.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: the words are processed by my ears and absorbed instantly into my brain.

currentSuggestions.original: I have to pay attention to the narrator, so I can't skim, look up references or think about a main idea while I drive.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: I have to pay attention to the narrator, so I can't skim, look up references or think about a main idea while I drive.

ops.insert: I have to pay attention to the narrator, so I can't skim, look up references or think about a main idea while I drive.

currentSuggestions.original: I think that for people who are sensitive to accents and cannot easily visualize the words on the page, listening to audiobooks is preferable.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: I think that for people who are sensitive to accents and cannot easily visualize the words on the page, listening to audiobooks is preferable.

currentSuggestions.original: As a result, I tend to scrutinize the narrator more because I enjoy the narrated book less.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: As a result, I tend to scrutinize the narrator more because I enjoy the narrated book less.

currentSuggestions.original: Still, there are times where listening to an audiobook is a better choice.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Still, there are times where listening to an audiobook is a better choice.

currentSuggestions.original: For example, I love accents.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: For example, I love accents.

ops.insert: As a result, I tend to scrutinize the narrator more because I enjoy the narrated book less.

currentSuggestions.original: Other than the above examples, I prefer reading.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Other than the above examples, I prefer reading.

currentSuggestions.original: Some books are natural to listen to.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: Some books are natural to listen to.

currentSuggestions.original: When I read I also get to reflect on what I am reading; I can pause and may prefer to do so.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: When I read I also get to reflect on what I am reading; I can pause and may prefer to do so.

currentSuggestions.original: When I read I can marvel at the prose of a writer, but when I listen, the prose is heard and not read.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: When I read I can marvel at the prose of a writer, but when I listen, the prose is heard and not read.

currentSuggestions.original: The author's mind, the author's time and energy, are both present and on display.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: The author's mind, the author's time and energy, are both present and on display.

currentSuggestions.original: The good reader, it is said, reads with a pen in hand.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: The good reader, it is said, reads with a pen in hand.

currentSuggestions.original: As mediators divert my attention to what they are forcing upon me, I am disconnected from my own mind that is stimulated with thought and imagination.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: As mediators divert my attention to what they are forcing upon me, I am disconnected from my own mind that is stimulated with thought and imagination.
